name: Congressman Kelly Armstrong
tweet_text: The Separation of Powers Act allows for the courts to reclaim their authority by reviewing agency actions under a de novo standard, so that judges can consider such issues solely on the merits. This removes the presumptive influences of agencies.

name: Congressman Kelly Armstrong
tweet_text: Mandated deference to agencies in the judicial review process hands agencies a tremendous power over the meaning of our laws, despite federal agencies not deriving their authority from the Constitution.

name: Congressman Kelly Armstrong
tweet_text: Chevron Deference requires that federal courts defer to statutory interpretations offered by federal agencies. The Constitution clearly gives the legislative power to Congress and judicial authority to the federal courts, not the bureaucracy.

name: Congressman Kelly Armstrong
tweet_text: It’s time to shrink the arsenal of an out-of-control federal bureaucracy, which is why I introduced H.R. 7895, the Separation of Powers Act. It would eliminate the judicial doctrine known as Chevron Deference, which empowers the federal bureaucracy.

name: Congressman Kelly Armstrong
tweet_text: Yet, we need to make it easier for law enforcement to identify bad actors, terminate them, and ensure they cannot simply be rehired at a different department.

name: Congressman Kelly Armstrong
tweet_text: We also need to recognize that the overwhelming majority of law enforcement officers are great people who serve their communities by performing a challenging and dangerous job. Any legislation cannot endanger them or sacrifice their safety.

name: Congressman Kelly Armstrong
tweet_text: Finally, we need to incentivize States to implement similar reforms because the vast majority of criminal justice occurs at the state and local level.

name: Congressman Kelly Armstrong
tweet_text: We also need to bring federal law enforcement into the 21st Century by requiring that they record interviews. Written interview notes are susceptible to abuse and bias.

name: Congressman Kelly Armstrong
tweet_text: We should also continue to reform sentencing, such as ensuring total drug weight and firearms enhancements do not apply to defendants who are not directly culpable.

name: Congressman Kelly Armstrong
tweet_text:

• address the trial penalty

• provide adequate resources for public defenders

• ensure that defendants receive all exculpatory evidence before a court can accept their guilty plea
